ncreases presence of thyroid hormone receptors","Works primarily by blocking thyroid hormone breakdown","Has a short half-life requiring multiple daily doses"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ELevothyroxine (T4) is a synthetic form of thyroid hormone that must be \u003Cstrong\u003Econverted to triiodothyronine (T3) in peripheral tissues\u003C/strong\u003E by deiodinase enzymes to exert its full biological effect. This conversion occurs primarily in the liver and kidneys.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELevothyroxine is a synthetic form of T4, not \u003Cstrong\u003Ea synthetic form of T3 and binds to thyroid hormone receptors \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases presence of thyroid hormone receptors \u003C/strong\u003Eis incorrect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWorks primarily by blocking thyroid hormone breakdown\u003C/strong\u003E - Levothyroxine functions as a direct hormone replacement and does not act by \u003Cstrong\u003Eblocking thyroid hormone breakdown.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELevothyroxine has a long, (not \u003Cstrong\u003Eshort)\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Ehalf-life \u003C/strong\u003Eof approximately 7 days, which enables once-daily dosing rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Emultiple daily doses.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAbsorption of levothyroxine is best on an empty stomach, as food and certain supplements (particularly calcium and iron) can interfere with its absorption.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Levothyroxine is converted to triiodothyronine in peripheral tissues by deiodinase enzymes.","Levothyroxine has a long half-life of 7 days which allows for once-daily dosing.","Le